During the Stash startup the {{/status}} resources returns

{code}
{
   "state": "ERROR"
}
{code}

instead of {{STARTING}} with an associated status code of {{500 Internal Server Error}}.

Could be a remnant of the split startup rework as the {{com.atlassian.stash.internal.web.ApplicationStatusServlet}} is unable to resolve the application context and resorts to returning an {{ERROR}} in this case.

{panel:title=Workaround}

There are currently three options available to work around this issue until https://rhn.redhat.com/errata/RHBA-2014-1797.html is fixed. 

# Use Oracle JDK 1.8
# Use Open JDK 1.7 (or a version prior to those listed in https://rhn.redhat.com/errata/RHBA-2014-1797.html) Our supported platforms matrix has been updated to reflect this.
# set jdk.tls.disabledAlgorithms=EC,ECDHE,ECDH in $JAVA_HOME/jre/lib/security/java.security on the broken OpenJDK 1.8

{panel}

